    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban the sale of non-biodegradable dog poo bags",
        "additional_details": "There are 8.9 million dogs in the UK. Many of the UK's dog owners use disposable, non-biodegradable dog poo bags on a regular basis. This use of plastic poses a grave risk to the environment, especially when not correctly disposed of. Biodegradable bags are readily available",
        "background": "Limit the sale of dog poo bags to those which biodegrade, in order to protect the environment.",
